race.comment: BILLIE BRONX (14) has an awkward barrier but will go close with average luck in the run. Resumed here with a big all-the-way win over 1200m in a 56, and then things didn't work out for the 4kg apprentice at Kyneton bet into $ 2.80. Meech goes aboard today and will likely push forward. Presents fitter and a bounce is on the cards. CASH CONVERTER (9) raced favourite over this trip on the same day beaten less than 2L. She missed a lip at Mornington prior and will be hard to beat.  KISS MY ROCK (7) resumes and is up to this if presented on song. At her best over a mile, but has placed fresh and deserves a betting watch. GREENHILL PRINCE (1) is racing well and rates a value chance in an open contest.
